result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel R Hockins was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01.
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Daniel R Hockins appears by phone from Arizona State Prison. Attorney Rick Brian Meier appears in person.  Colleen Catherine Nordin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Atty Meier and defendant ready to proceed with plea to resolve matter if court willing to do so by phone. Court will to take plea by phone as all parties are in agreement. Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Cts. 1, 2, 3, 5 & 6. Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of Cts. 1, 2, 3, 5 & 6.  Court dismisses Ct. 4 but reads in for sentencing. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Defendant apologizes to the victim and the court. Atty Meier will mail appeal right to defendant. Bond is no longer in effect.
Cash bond signed by defendant on 1/29/18 and notarized by Kathleen Fry.
Atty Meier indicates cash bond will be posted, monies being forwarded to him to post for defendant.  Bond form given to Atty Meier to send to defendant for signature.

Defense waives reading of Information, stands mute regarding the charges. Court enters not guilty plea on defendants behalf. Court willing to take a plea by phone if all parties are in agreement.  Court cancels warrant. Bond set.

Defendant Daniel R Hockins appears by phone from Arizona State Prison-Douglas/Mohave. Attorney Rick Brian Meier appears in person.  Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file.  Atty Meier indicates defendant wishes to waive his right to a preliminary hearing today.  Defense waives right to Prelim. Court questions defendant on waiver. Court finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver and binds over for trial. Court finds probable cause for bindover.  Status conference scheduled for March 27, 2018 at 09:30 am.
Adjustment Number: 18A 004418, Payable Number: 82898, Receipt Number: 18R 000274, Amount: $20.00
VW - Victim Impact Statement of Shawn Hockins

Defendant Daniel R Hockins appeared by phone from Arizona prison. Colleen Catherine Nordin appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews charges, max penalties, right to prelim, issuance of warrant, filings by Defendant. Court questions Defendant, who doesn't know what he wants to do, has been in prison for 3 years, had substance abuse problem. Court warns Defendant against making statements against his interest, strongly encourages Defendant to contact PD's office, reviews possibility of waiver of right to counsel to try to resolve matter with DA or hiring private counsel. Defendant wants representation, is given phone number for PD's office. Defendant will appear by phone for next hearing.  Status conference scheduled for January 18, 2018 at 11:15 am.
